  "prompt": "Which food should I not eat after getting a tattoo?",
  "response": "After getting a tattoo, you should avoid or limit certain foods that can interfere with the healing process:\n\n1. Avoid foods that can thin your blood:\n- Alcohol\n- Aspirin\n- Fish oil supplements\n- Foods high in omega-3 fatty acids\n\n2. Limit sugary and processed foods:\n- These can slow down healing\n- May increase inflammation\n\n3. Stay away from spicy foods:\n- Can potentially irritate the tattoo\n- May cause discomfort during healing\n\n4. Minimize high-sodium foods:\n- Can cause swelling\n- May slow down healing\n\nInstead, focus on:\n- Drinking plenty of water\n- Eating foods rich in vitamins A and C\n- Consuming protein to support healing\n- Eating foods with zinc\n- Consuming foods that reduce inflammation\n\nAlways follow your tattoo artist's specific aftercare instructions and consult them if you have any concerns about your diet during the healing process.",
